The AQECC algorithm uses a machine learning approach to adapt to changes in the error rates and noise characteristics. The algorithm can be summarized as follows:
1. Train a machine learning model to predict the optimal error correction parameters based on the error rates and noise characteristics.
2. Use the trained model to predict the optimal error correction parameters for the current error rates and noise characteristics.
3. Update the error correction parameters using the predicted values.
4. Repeat steps 1-3 until the desired level of error correction is achieved.
